text: I have the script working that saves the template to the server. we will be able to just host it all from the head node. it will work better from there anyways. for right now what i have setup is you will be able to bring up the editor from there on your computer. make a template, and hit save, that saves it to the headnode. then you will need to hit F5 on the headnode to refresh the page, and that will load the new template. I am finishing up a script that will allow you to upload images also. Then anyone can go over and push to the headnode. It will be locked to a specific template that you will be overwriting for now. we can get fancier with that function later if we need to. but for now it will allow very simple testing and pushing of images and design to the test rig
dont think will have enough time to completely finish this tonight, but will get very close and will have it finished in the morning for sure.
and touch is getting close, as well the display for the 3 monitors is nearly up
<@U0EL0GLEL>: send that to joel and i for clean up and getting it to dev
Send what? I'm not done with what in working on
im saying dont unleash it on the masses, unleash it on me to sort out/figure out socialize
Sure can, expecting to finish and test out in the morning. probably finish before leaving, install and test first thing tomorrow. then we can show it at stand up or around there
